replies.body:
Even so grevous wounds from ignite, mortal reminder, and morellonomicon will still lower the amount of healing RoA grants him.  if you CC him during his ult or use {{item:3165}}  and {{item:3033}} and deliver burst to him I very much doubt he'll survive. RoA also can't really keep you up in mana by losing HP, or keep your HP by using mana. Eventually you'll run out of one of them to use and his ult is very costly in terms of mana. 

The heal from RoA is kinda small anyways. I mean it's enough to make a difference in the laning phase but when it comes to team fights I doubt it'll do much in the long run beyond saving you with a very small portion of HP left.

I think this change gives a bigger buff to {{champion:13}} and {{champion:27}}
